library(tidyverse)
##  Attaching packages  tidyverse 1.3.1 
##  ggplot2 3.3.5      purrr   0.3.4
##  tibble  3.1.4      dplyr   1.0.7
##  tidyr   1.1.3      stringr 1.4.0
##  readr   2.0.1      forcats 0.5.1
##  Conflicts  tidyverse_conflicts() 
## x dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()
## x dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
data <- data %>% 
  select(school, sex, age, address, famsize, Dalc, Walc)
head(data)
##   school sex age address famsize Dalc Walc
## 1     GP   F  18       U     GT3    1    1
## 2     GP   F  17       U     GT3    1    1
## 3     GP   F  15       U     LE3    2    3
## 4     GP   F  15       U     GT3    1    1
## 5     GP   F  16       U     GT3    1    2
## 6     GP   M  16       U     LE3    1    2
data %>% 
  group_by(school) %>% 
  summarize(count=n())
## # A tibble: 2  2
##   school count
##   <chr>  <int>
## 1 GP       349
## 2 MS        46
data1 <- data %>% 
  group_by(Dalc, school) %>% 
  summarize(count=n(), .groups="drop") %>% 
  mutate(total=case_when(school=="GP"~349, 
                         school=="MS"~46)) %>% 
  mutate(p=count/total)
data1 %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(aes(Dalc, p, fill=school), position="dodge", stat="identity") +
  ggtitle("Proportion of Students in Each Weekday Consumption Level by School") + 
  ylab("Proportion") +
  xlab("Weekday Consumption Level")
